a_n = 3 + 3*a_{n-1} Let's unroll the recurrence: a_n = 3 + 3*a_{n-1}
a_{n-1} = 3 + 3*a_{n-2}
Substitute into a_n: a_n = 3 + 3*(3 + 3*a_{n-2}) = 3 + 9 + 9*a_{n-2} = 12 + 9*a_{n-2}
Similarly, a_{n-2} = 3 + 3*a_{n-3}
So, a_n = 3 + 3*(3 + 3*a_{n-3}) = 3 + 9 + 9*a_{n-3} = 12 + 9*a_{n-3}
Continuing this pattern, after k steps, a_n = 3*(3^{k} - 1)/(3 - 1) + 3^{k}*a_{n - k}
